5:
Are you really sure I'm the right
person to bring? Nimbus would
make a much better sparring
partner!
10:
No, no! Our training is no mere
brawl! On the contrary, your
presence is most needed, Alk.
14:
Take care of those vegetables for
me, would you?
16:
My, you're so efficient, Zantetsu!
Such a big help.
Serve it up once it's simmered for a
while.
24: Would you care for a taste?
28:
...That's seriously good! Have you
been practicing?
32:
Heheh. You flatter me. A dish like this
is nothing!
37:
So, why the interest in cooking all of
a sudden?
41:
...I wished to imitate you, Lord Alk. To
broaden my horizons with the craft
of cooking.
43:
That is what a hero should aspire to
do, after all!
48:
I'm honored to hear that, but... I don't
know. Something about your
reasoning feels off.
59:
Ha! Cry all you want—there is no one
to help you! Rue your carelessness
for the short remainder of your
miserable life!
61:
Not another move!
I am Zantetsu, ninja samurai and
warrior of justice! Prepare to receive
your judgment!
64:
Is this one of the movies you were
talking about?
68:
Indeed. I was overcome with a
desire to watch it again. It's been a
while since I last did so.
73:
Pretty neat that you can just watch
movies like that.
Hey, aren't the actors in this all
humans?
77:
This is a movie from a time before
androids existed—excavated from
the melted earth created by the
rains of fire that destroyed our world.
80:
Getting my hands on uncensored
data like this was my specialty, you
see.
87:
I see... So the name, the persona, 
it's all from this movie?
91: That it is! My origin... and my zenith.
95: You really are just like him.
102:
One who seeks glory in the slaying
of a monster instead of saving
injured villagers? Am I truly like the
great Zantetsu?
106:
Leaving the monster alone wasn't
an option at the time, though.
110:
And yet Lady Stella leapt into the
fight to rescue them, risking all. I, on
the other hand, chose to fight the
monster.
113:
In the heat of the battle, that was
the decision I made.
122:
In that very moment, I knew the
truth—I am not a true ninja samurai.
125:
No, I am merely playing pretend—a
droid content to change out body
parts and pose as a hero.
127:
I'm nothing but a copy-pasted
version of another. An imposter.
131: Is imitating others really that bad?
139:
I cannot merely imitate. In order to
become a true hero, one must
change—adapt... That is why I
started on this path to begin with.
145: Well, what are you going to do then?
148:
Are you going to stop being a ninja
samurai?
156: The truth is... I do not wish to give up.
163:
If you keep going, you might find
one day that you've actually
changed!
165:
Until that day, you keep working at it
and continue your training. Just like
the guy in the movie said!
169:
I am no warrior of justice... My heart
is an empty vessel, desperate to be
filled.
172:
Despite this, you would allow me to
accompany you on your journey?
177:
Of course! You know, we're not all
that different. I'm missing something
too—my memories.
186:
Lord Alk... It is an honor most great to
be by your side. I am endlessly
thankful.
189:
Come on, you're exaggerating. It's
no big deal! Let's do our best
together, Zantetsu.
195:
I'll act as bait. You run while they're
distracted!
197:
No! I would never do that! We have
to leave together—
210:
I am Zantetsu, ninja samurai and
warrior of justice! Prepare to receive
your judgment!
213:
Y-you wiped them all out in one
blow! Thank you, Mr. Zantetsu!
218:
You were on fire today, you know.
Are you feeling any better about...
that thing we talked about before?
228:
Yeah, fair enough. Change doesn't
come that quickly.
231:
I am blind to what the future holds
for me...
234:
But no matter what lies waiting for
me at the end of all these trials and
tribulations, I shall face it head on.
242:
However long a time that may
require, I implore you, Lord Alk:
Walk this path with me.
